<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="42" type="diagnose">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="42">Diagnose.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="42">Frons slightly longer than wide (33:28). Femora black, tibiae and tarsi entirely yellow. Wing hyaline without a brown spot near wing apex. Surstylus short, nearly triangular. Pregonite as long as postgonite.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="42" type="distribution.">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="42">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="42">China; Pakistan.</paragraph>
